name: weaned calves production on pasture | weaned calves, live weight | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/21618/documentation

This dataset was built as a weighted average of regional datasets of the same activityName.  Weights are based on production volumes.;BR: production volume = 6.18e+08 kg/year, weight = 0.5998;ZA: production volume = 4.12e+08 kg/year, weight = 0.4002

This activity starts at the replanting of pasture.

This activity ends with the provision of weaned calves at farm gate, ready to be sent to slaughterhouses as live weight.
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/01:Crop and animal production, hunting and related service activities/014:Animal production/0141:Raising of cattle and buffaloes

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Time period of the most of the data collected for this dataset.
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: This dataset is a weighted average built from the following geographies: BR, ZA.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Pasture is regularly fertilized and replanted every 20 years. Mineral salt is served as supplement feed for all cattle in troughs on the field. Besides pasture and mineral salt, no suplement is served to cattle. The dataset does not include pharmaceuticals, although typical production systems use them. Use of hormones for cattle raising is forbidden in Brazil.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Carbon content, water and gross calorific value are based on ecoinvent database.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Weighted average of Brazilian and South african data.
